---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { business } from "../data/business";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | KOM USA" description="Learn what information KOM USA collects through kom-usa.com, why it is used, and how to contact us about your information.">
  <section class="section-pad bg-kom-warm-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
      <p class="font-extrabold text-kom-field">Last updated July 14, 2026</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-kom-charcoal-deep sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-kom-charcoal/75">This policy explains how {business.legalName}, operating as {business.name}, handles information submitted through kom-usa.com.</p>

      <div class="article-body mt-10 text-kom-charcoal/75">
        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <p>A service, estimate, or contact request may include your name, phone number, email address, property address or ZIP code, service selection, preferred contact method, timing, project description, and any other details you choose to provide. The form also records the source page and campaign tags in the page address so we can understand which requests came from the website.</p>
        <p>Our hosting and security providers may automatically receive routine technical information such as an IP address, browser type, device type, requested page, and date and time of access.</p>

        <h2>How we use information</h2>
        <p>We use submitted information to review your request, determine the appropriate Maintenance or Construction team, contact you about the requested work, prepare or discuss an estimate, provide service, prevent abuse, and understand how the website is being used.</p>
        <p>Submitting a service request does not add you to a marketing list. If KOM USA later offers optional marketing email or text messages, that permission will be requested separately.</p>

        <h2>Service providers and sharing</h2>
        <p>Information may be processed by providers that help us operate the website and respond to requests. The current website uses Netlify for hosting and form processing, Brevo for request routing and acknowledgement email, Sanity for website content, and Google services for maps and review information. These providers process information under their own terms and privacy practices.</p>
        <p>We do not sell personal information. We may share information with contractors or service professionals when needed to review or perform the work you requested, and when required by law or necessary to protect the website, business, customers, or public.</p>

        <h2>Maps, reviews, and outside websites</h2>
        <p>Pages that display a Google map or link to Google reviews, Instagram, or another outside service may allow that service to receive technical information when you load or visit it. Their privacy policies govern their own collection and use.</p>

        <h2>Retention and security</h2>
        <p>We keep request and project information for as long as reasonably needed to respond, provide service, maintain business and tax records, resolve disputes, and meet legal obligations. KOM USA and its providers use practical safeguards, but no website, email, or storage system can be guaranteed completely secure.</p>

        <h2>Your choices</h2>
        <p>You may ask to review, correct, or delete information you submitted by emailing <a href={business.emailHref}>{business.email}</a>. Some records may need to be retained for contracts, warranties, accounting, fraud prevention, or other legal obligations.</p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>This website is intended for adults requesting property services. KOM USA does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 through this website.</p>

        <h2>Policy changes</h2>
        <p>We may update this policy when the website, service providers, or business practices change. The date at the top shows the latest posted version.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about this policy or website information can be sent to <a href={business.emailHref}>{business.email}</a> or discussed by calling <a href={business.phoneHref}>{business.phone}</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
